metadata:
  section_id: 12
  section_name: رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کے پاپوش مبارک کا بیان
  hadith_first: 74
  hadith_last: 84

hadiths[10]{hadithnumber,text,grades,reference,international_number,narrator_chain,chapter_intro}:
74,"‘How were the sandals of Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace)?’ He said: ‘They had two thongs'.”",,,74,"Qatada said; “I asked Anas ibn Malik:",رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کے پاپوش مبارک کا بیان
75,"""The sandals of Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) had two thongs with double laces.”",,,75,"Ibn 'Abbas said:",رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کے پاپوش مبارک کا بیان
76,"""Anas ibn Malik brought out to us a pair of hairless sandals with two thongs. Then Thabit told me afterwards, on the authority of Anas, that they were the sandals of the Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace).”",,,76,"'Isa ibn Tahman said:",رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کے پاپوش مبارک کا بیان
77,"""I saw you wearing the tanned ox-hide sandals with no hair on them [an-ni'al as-sibtiyya]."" He replied:\n""I saw Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) wearing the sandals on which there is no hair, and he performed the minor ritual ablution in them, so I love to wear them!”",,,77,"'Ubaid ibn Juraij said to Ibn 'Umar:",رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کے پاپوش مبارک کا بیان
78,"""The sandals of Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) had two thongs.""",,,78,"Abu Huraira said:",رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کے پاپوش مبارک کا بیان
79,"""I saw Allah's Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) performing the ritual prayer in sewn sandals.”",,,79,"Amr ibn Huraith said:",رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کے پاپوش مبارک کا بیان
80,“Let none of you walk in a single sandal. Let him wear them both or take them both off!”,,,80,"Abu Hurairah reports that Allah’s Messenger said (Allah bless him and give him peace):",رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کے پاپوش مبارک کا بیان
82,"“The Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) forbade one (referring to the man) to eat with his left hand, or to walk in a single sandal.”",,,82,"Jabir reported:",رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کے پاپوش مبارک کا بیان
83,"“The Prophet said (Allah bless him and give him peace): ""When one of you puts on sandals, let him begin with the right, and when he takes them off, let him begin with the left, for the right must be the first of them to be put on, and the last of them to be taken off.”",,,83,"Abu Huraira said:",رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کے پاپوش مبارک کا بیان
84,"""Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) would love to start whatever he could on the right side, in his combing, his footwear and his purification.”",,,84,"'A’isha said:",رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کے پاپوش مبارک کا بیان
